  "version": "HL7 v2.3",
  "chapter": "Patient Administration",
  "description": "An A49 event is used to signal a change of an incorrectly assigned account number value. The “incorrect source account number” value is stored in the MRG segment (MRG-3-prior patient account number) and is to be changed to the “correct target account number” value stored in the PID segment (PID-18-patient account number).\n\nA change has been done at the account identifier level. That is, a PID-18-patient account number has been found to be incorrect and has been changed.",
